This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) techniques for gaze estimation, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV sub-category. The use of a generative adversarial network (GAN) also suggests that it may belong to the cs.LG sub-category, which deals with machine learning techniques. The potential applications in human-computer interaction (HCI) and accessibility suggest that it may also belong to the cs.HC sub-category, which deals with human-computer interaction and user-centered design. The use of mobile devices suggests that it may also belong to the cs.GR sub-category, which deals with graphics and visualization. Finally, the use of image synthesis techniques suggests that it may also belong to the cs.MM sub-category, which deals with multimedia and multimodal processing.
